    "intro": "Nebraska residential leases are governed by the **Uniform Residential Landlord and Tenant Act** (URLTA), codified at Neb. Rev. Stat. §§ 76-1401 through 76-1449. The Act sets a mandatory floor of tenant protections that **no lease clause can waive**, and it requires landlords to disclose ownership and management information in writing before the tenancy begins. Getting the lease right from the start avoids unenforceable provisions and the statutory damages tenants can recover when landlords deliberately include prohibited terms.",
