      "Security deposit terms: if a deposit is collected, the lease must confirm it does not exceed one month's rent (plus up to one-quarter month's rent for pets) per § 76-1416, and that it will be itemized and returned within 14 days of move-out.",
      "Landlord's maintenance obligations: the lease should reflect the landlord's non-waivable duty under § 76-1419 to maintain the unit in a fit and habitable condition, make required repairs, and keep common areas safe.",
      "Tenant's maintenance obligations: the lease should state the tenant's duties under § 76-1421, including keeping the unit clean, disposing of waste properly, and not deliberately damaging the property.",
      "Notice requirements: the lease must specify the required written notice periods for entry (at least 24 hours under § 76-1423 except in emergencies) and for termination of a month-to-month tenancy (30 days under § 76-1437).",
      "Domestic violence early-termination right: the lease should acknowledge that a tenant who is a victim of domestic violence may terminate early under § 76-1431.01 upon proper written notice and documentation."
